This product reads from open-data Earth observation providers via anonymous
HTTPS Range requests (no API keys, no operator credentials needed):

  * Copernicus DEM 30m       — © DLR, ESA — open under proprietary licence
                                with no fees and no usage restrictions
                                (https://spacedata.copernicus.eu/web/cscda/data-offer)
  * JRC Global Surface Water — © European Commission, JRC, 2021
                                (CC-BY 4.0 derivative attribution)
  * Hansen Global Forest Change — © Hansen / UMD / Google / USGS / NASA
                                (open access, attribution requested)
  * ESA WorldCover            — © ESA WorldCover project
                                (CC-BY 4.0)
  * GHSL                      — © European Commission, JRC
                                (CC-BY 4.0)
  * WorldPop                  — © University of Southampton, WorldPop
                                (CC-BY 4.0)
  * OpenStreetMap             — © OpenStreetMap contributors
                                (Open Database License — ODbL 1.0)

When emem returns a fact derived from any of these sources, the source
metadata is propagated through the signed receipt and the
`/v1/sources` manifest so downstream consumers can carry the attribution
forward.
